research_results: What are the key sustainability goals and plans for the next five years?: The key sustainability goals and plans for the next five years include protecting, more sustainably managing, or restoring at least 50 million acres of land and 1 million square miles of ocean by 2030, fostering more sustainable production of commodities, transitioning operations toward regenerative practices, supporting conservation and restoration of critical ecosystems, and encouraging the development of place-based initiatives. Additionally, there is a goal to source at least 20 agricultural commodities more sustainably by 2025.
